    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnmaterialproperty/1395372-contents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " value for this material property must be a 3D color lookup table, or a 2D texture image that represents such a table arranged in a horizontal strip. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A lookup table is a cube of color values: the red, green, and blue components of an input color map to the x, y, and z coordinates of a location in that cube, and at that location in the cube is a corresponding output color. You can provide data in this cubic format as a Metal texture with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/metal/mtltexturetype/mtltexturetype3d"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " texture type."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The 2D representation of a 3D color cube is an arrangement of slices: for example, a 16 x 16 x 16 color cube becomes a horizontal strip of 16 squares, each 16 x 16 pixels (that is, a 256 x 16 image). Each square contains a gradation of red and green components, and together the 16 squares form a gradation for the blue component. To provide a 2D representation of a color cube, set this material property’s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scnmaterialproperty/1395372-contents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " value to an image."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By using a color table, you can easily create custom color effects that apply to an entire rendered scene:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Create a basic color table image such as "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "link-media-1965935"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ", where the color value for each R, G, and B coordinate in the cube is the corresponding RGB color."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "image",
                      "identifier": "media-1965935",
                      "metadata": {
                        "anchor": "1965935",
                        "title": "Figure 1",
                        "abstract": [
                          {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Basic color table image"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Use an image editor to create the color effect you want using some other image—such as a screenshot of your game. Apply only effects that affect pixel colors without modifying pixel positions. (For example, you can use hue/saturation, color curves, or color matrix filters, but not blur or distort filters.)"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "image",
                      "identifier": "media-1965936",
                      "metadata": {
                        "anchor": "1965936",
                        "title": "Figure 2",
                        "abstract": [
                          {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Creating a color grading effect"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Apply the same color effect you created in step 2 to your basic color table image. You can even perform these steps together: paste the basic color table into your game screenshot, apply an effect to the combined picture, then crop the picture to just the modified color table. "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "link-media-1965936"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " shows an example effect."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Assign your customized color table image (such as the example in "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": false,
                      "identifier": "link-media-1965937"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ") to this property. When rendering, SceneKit looks up the RGB values for each pixel in the rendered scene, and displays the corresponding color values from the color table."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "image",
                      "identifier": "media-1965937",
                      "metadata": {
                        "anchor": "1965937",
                        "title": "Figure 3",
                        "abstract": [
                          {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "Custom color table image for color grading"
                          }
                        ]
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To enable this behavior, you must first enable the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/scenekit/scncamera/1644101-wantshdr"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " setting. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
